*[http://ixbtlabs.com/articles/trendware80211b/ On iXBT Labs] product roundup - the device shares the same manuf as early [[Buffalo]] devices. :The layout looks near identical to the [[Buffalo WLAR-L11-L]] and is probably the [[Buffalo WLA-L11]]. :It appears ''Buffalo / Melco'' manufactured the device as the device. It also carries a ''Buffalo'' OUI :(00:40:26) in the web configuration interface screenshots. The WLAN OUI is 00:60:1D (''[[Lucent]]''). :The device obviously seems to have been resold by ''[[BroMax]]'' (now merged into ''[[CyberTAN]]''), :however, as the device carries (in the web UI) the ''FreePort'' brand and the model ''WS200-LF''.
The default SSID may be 'APXXXXXX', where 'XXXXXX' is some combination of hex digits :(upper case letters).
